==English==

===Etymology===
[[in-]] not + [[dispensable]]: confer French ''[[indispensable]]''

===Adjective===
'''indispensable'''
# Not dispensable; impossible to be omitted, remitted, or spared; absolutely necessary or requisite.
# (Ecclesistical) Not admitting dispensation; not subject to release or exemption.
#:''The law was moral and '''indispensable'''.''  -Bp. Burnet
# {{obsolete}}: Unavoidable; inevitable.


